<br>
 I've had 4 petitions total in the year I've been playing EQ-2 on this server, which were handled promptly and courteously, and 2 on Tribunal, only one of which was answered and fixed (text from an NPC was wrong. Had to misspell a word to get the quest triggered). The other was some minor items that poofed when I was transfering them to the bank and went LD. Never did get an answer to that one. Not a big deal in my world. But, there has been a noticible decline in the timeliness (sp?) of answers to requests since SOE eliminated so many GM's.<br>
<br>
 Severine does raise some valid points about the lack of integrity in customer service for EQ. So, you want to charge $40 dollars for a name change, which is being done for free now. Inform your customers of the new policy-don't lie to the guides and say it's become impossible to do so, for programming reasons, and then start charging money for a sevice that was previously free. It makes the guides and GM's look like they are part of a conspiracy to rip off the paying customers. That is something I would take exception to, myself.<br>
<br>
Maybe the guides on this server are so much nicer, because they don't have to deal with the whiny ass riff-raff that exist on the blue servers. <br>
