<br>
For the most part -- one on one -- GMs are pretty good.  After playing on Legends, though, you really learn about the good ones and the bad ones.  Some of the processes VI has in place are really awful, too.  For instance, did you know that if you complain about a GM the compaint gets routed to the GM and not his superior?  Guess what the GM does with it?  Also, GMs pretty much make up the rules as they go along.  They are often completely unaware of the published rules (a guildie has screenshots of a GM asking where the rules were posted and she wasn't joking).<br>
<br>
